reviews.text:
The "help" I received as a student from the office of the registrar today was just downright awful. I've been struggling as a transfer student to adjust to a quarter-based 10-week system. I'm used to a 15-week semester-based system. I've had a hard time learning these time constraints and ran into issues withdrawing from a couple of classes this term. Not only do they have a withdrawal deadline (for what? That is different than my past institutions) but if you want to drop a class past that deadline you're out of luck, even if it means failing it! Yep, even if it's your first ever withdrawal, they won't let you do it. For a class YOU PAID FOR! 

Not only that, but the man "helping" me at the registrar talked down to me IN PUBLIC IN THE OPEN OFFICE IN FRONT OF OTHER STUDENTS! He berated me for "waiting too long," even though I've had to work 40+ hour weeks and have tried contacting professors to no avail. 

This hasn't been my first issue and I'm sure it's not my last with UO.  If you're looking for a university that offers you options, look elsewhere. UO will shut you down at your first attempt. They are more concerned about lining their pockets with $ rather than student success.
walking around eugene can be a little sketchy, but the school has a nice mix of new and old buildings and lovely quads
Best School in the world for sure.
THE Best School Ever!
UO police deportment and secertity guards are biased against the poor and homeless.....and they bully the poor and homeless ....when is the bullying going to end????
Wouldnt recommend this for a first time hockey goer, reminded me of a B rated hockey movie. Just sad that those young players have to play in that environment.
Best kept secret in town.  Great family event.  High energy and excitement.
Great atmosphere.   Wonderful events.  The Generals are the best kept secret in Town.
Fun time!
Great

This is a great little venue nestled right into downtown Eugene. First time visiting tonight to see a set of local bands and I really enjoyed it! The place itself has a lot of character and ambiance and the audio mix was superb and not too loud. They even had an underground bar with local brews! Only downside is not being able to take the drinks up to where the bands are playing but they have a live camera and audio mix to the basement so you can finish your drink and not miss the show too much. Was a great place to spend an evening, definitely will be coming back!

Interesting concert venue with a unique feel. Good place to catch a decent show for cheap. In order to get a beer/drink you have to go downstairs and the beverage must be consumed downstairs so you can not drink while watching the show.

Good venue, except for one critical flaw: inadequate restrooms for the capacity. There were long lines for both men and women pretty much all night. Not a big deal until you need one, but quite a big deal when you do. Seems like they could at least supply some portables for bigger events.
Love the "think outside the box/realize there is no box" acts they allow here! A teuly one-of-a-kind  venue like NO other.
I was here for the weekend. Thought I would attend a gig to expeirence the North East Coast vibe! I was not disappointed. Great venue, great crowd.

There is a lot of incredibly cool art here.  You wouldn't think a small town like Eugene could build up a museum like this, but they did.  Definitely worth a visit.  Some cool places  nearby to grab a bite are an extra plus.
Call ahead if you want/need to go. They are almost never open for all of their business hours. Exhibits are fine, but not worth paying for so if you aren’t a student don’t bother.
A beautiful museum in a great location. A fantastic exhibit on Chinese and Japanese artwork. New modern exhibits every few months. Cafe inside with courtyard as well.
Phenomenal Chinese art, great gallery at excellent bang for your buck. Definitely recommend if you are headed towards campus at all!
Great place with a constant stream of new media

Quite high quality professional theatre -- a play with impact, well-acted.  The lighting and set were right for the play, but a little tedious to look at for 90 minutes.  More sound and lighting effects might have helped.  Luckily the two main actors were expressive even when not speaking.  The play did make us question assumptions as it took its twists and turns.  The theatre space is great -- no bad seats and it's nice to be allowed to bring drinks and food in.  We'll be back, even from an hour away.
Every play I've seen here was entertaining. The theatre is small enough there isn't a bad seat in the house. As the name suggests, a great place to sample modern theatre.

I absolutely loved every part of the show! From the gorgeous set upon entering the theater, to the costume design, the direction, the lighting, and of course the fantastic acting from each and every cast member! ( not to mention the gorgeous music played by Sabrina gross on piano!) They truly told a beautiful story from all angles and put me, along with everyone  who was a part of opening night, into a wonderful place in heart and mind🙏🏼  A must see holiday show… You won’t be disappointed unless you miss the show! 
Thank you to the Oregon contemporary Theatre for bringing the show to life on stage🙏🏼🎭💝
Storm
Love that I won a Meiji Izakaya coupon there the one time a friend of mine took me there.
NW 10: a wonderful selection of plays that were hilarious, thought-provoking and highly entertaining.

Good atmosphere could use some fresher popcorn. seating was somewhat uncomfortable. Unique experience and unique movies. Wasn't terrible but could be a bit better. Broadway metro was more comfortable and felt a little more movie theater like. Still recomend it regardless! Garlic popcorn was good!

Lovely theater! I really enjoyed the smaller atmosphere than the huge mall theaters and I hope that Bijou Art Cinemas is around for many more years! Food prices were more realistic/reasonable and they have a better variety than anywhere else. (Menu available online) Check this place out, you won't be disappointed!

Cozy, atmospheric art-house cinema with delicious popcorn and very friendly workers! I recently attended a screening of a singalong version of Bohemian Rhapsody with my boyfriend and it was a blast! The ticket/concessions clerk even gave us a free bag of popcorn after the screening 😄 I highly recommend this local gem!

I love the building, the people, the movie offerings and the refreshments (priced reasonably). The only thing I would change (and this is purely a "it's your problem") is the width of the seats and leg room in Theater Two.  I am 6'2" and overweight.  The good side?  If, for some reason the seat would go flying through the air, I would not need a seat belt. But they have kindly placed a back "row" of chairs with a decorative pillows with plenty of room for both. 😉😁
There is more than ample leg room  and comfortable seats in Theater One.  👍👍

Best movie theater ever. In an old church sanctuary. Also I think its funny that that woman couldn't tell the difference between Lady Bird and Three Billboards for half an hour and blames it on you lol.
I run up there every time I'm in town. Great inspiration Eugene legend
Great piece of American History. Sad ending to an exceptional athlete and icon.
I been woodtreating the powerlines up there and its just a cool place always shady

RIP Pre.  It took 15 years to get here, but well worth it.  The roads going up to the memorial wind forever and are very tight.  Drive with caution and be mindful of the wildlife.  The marker is very well done and kept up.  There is three small alcove to park in close to the rock.  If those are full, there is Rhododendron Park just down the street with a few more spots.  The park has a small trail and is a must see when visiting Pre's rock.  The rock is not a bad jog from the park.  I'm very glad I was able to see this before I died.  Thank you Pre for showing how to run with heart.
It's a nice guys's stone! But I think it is too simple to be placed so lonely or rough!
What a delightful place for dinner.  My whole family enjoyed their dinner. I would highly recommend

Great food quality, but not a great value. Large bowl of soup was flavorful, and my granddaughter enjoyed her yumm bowl, but with mini service and self cleared tables, I expected better pricing.  I'll know better next time what to expect

I love to visit when I am in Eugene. They offer a healthy alternative to fast food at a great price. Theirfood is great and it even caters to my vegitarian daughter while making those who prefer a little meat happy too. Their name is so fitting!
Love Cafe yumm!! Always delicious and such great friendly service 😋💫🌟💞
Always Yummy at Cafe Yummu!  Very pleasant and friendly Cashier and server!  Congratulations on new Idaho Cafes!  Good service, Good growth!

Mezza Luna is very satisfying! There are a variety of vegetarian and meat eater slices available under $4, massive(!) salads that are amazing, and beer. Also on menu is full pizzas, appetizers, and gf options. The vibe in there is pretty chill but pleasant. The service when we went in was exceptional and friendly. Great for lunch or dinner! I would advise to plan where you're parking in advance.
Best pizza in town. They don't skimp on the toppings, the crust is super tasty and the staff are friendly. Also the fresh level of their salads is off the chain.

Delicious pizza! Amazing salads! Best staff! By the slice or whole pie. Mezza Luna often wins Best of Eugene Awards. Lots of vegetarian options. Gluten free option (that actually tastes pretty good) 3 beers on tap with rotating options. I loved to study here when I was in college. Can have its busy rushes but overall mellow and chill place for a slice and beverage.

The only thing more awesome than their pizza is their hustle.
  I have a soft spot for kitchen clairvoyance as I worked in a local bakery for 3 years. 

Seeing them juggling multiple orders with epic peel game when I pick up mine inspires me to continue being awesome at all I do.

I sometimes even buy their cheesy-bacon-gnots to go with homemade pizza.

Food is good and unique but they have this new rule that you can’t get a door dash or grub hub order without your bag which the pizza doesn’t even fit in the bag so I will just not order from there anymore.
I love this place. Amazing hamburgers. I try to get a different one every time - and I'm  always surprised how good it is. Service is good, atmosphere is quaint. Yummy!
This was one if the best burgers I've ever had in Eugene. The service was great and despite being fairly busy it wasn't so loud that I could no hear anyone. Totally worth while. 9/10 will eat again.
I love this place. The food is great and the service is friendly. Plus they have great beers to compliment there awesome burgers!!!
i heard your going to come to Cave Junction, if its true i would like to apply for a job with you,, i have excelent experience
Had a great late brunch there, loved the service too!
Excellent quality and prices. Very friendly staff. Popular place, limited seating so most take out. Fast service. Yummy, fresh.
Hands down the best burritos in town and they even have the best curly fries! Super random but amazing. Love their sauces. Large menu, lots of options. Good prices. Good quick eats.
Some of the best burritos in town. Good prices. Great friendly service. I come here weekly and its consistent decliciousness!!
I find myself craving this place constantly. And the price is unbeatable for how good the food is.
Delicious food and accompaniments. Try the namesake burrito. A lot of bang for your buck.

Came here while visiting my sister and I have to say it was a great little diner. I got the corned beef hash and it was buttery and crispy on the outside and soft and savory on the inside. Got a side of biscuits and gravy as well. The biscuit way huge and immensely fluffy. You should definitely come visit this greasy spoon!

Great food. Pricing is fair. Service is usually fast, but the popularity of this place can bring long wait times on their busy days. The addition of a full espresso menu raises the bar for diner coffee. I had the hangover special, it was just what the doctor ordered.

Great service! Food was really good, I got a veggie egg Benedict with a veggie sausage. Perfect! Love your waitress to btw I needed to breastfeed and she was super supportive and tried to keep my privacy

We were waited on my the owner, Joy. She works as hard as her employees. She is a real joy!
Food was excellent.
Quick and tasty classic dinner food. Small Town service with a smile and good portion sizes. A local staple.
Delicious meal, exquisitely presented. Small portions, but that is what I expect from a fancy place like this. Very cozy and romantic. Great location in the hopping 5th Street Market.

The giant hot chocolate they boast about was very disappointing. Yes it was a bowl of hot chocolate but it was so bitter that I barely wanted to drink any of it. Last time I checked hot chocolate is supposed to be sweet not bland and bitter. It has an open kitchen design which seemed cool at first until the manager or someone was constantly yelling at the kitchen staff to quiet down. I honestly preferred the kitchen chatter over the managers voice.
Fantastic food and amazing staff. Absolutely world class food. I've had everything on the menu and I have never been disappointed. It's always a pleasure dining here
I didn't know we had a 4 star restaurant in Eugene! Food was great. Service was excellent. Thanks very much for a memorable evening. Good job!

The food here is simply fantastic, but the real charm of this place is the service. Our waitperson was so knowledgable about everything on the menu and what cocktail or wine would go with it, that you would swear she was actually the chef. Six of us kind of just showed up with a convoluted reservation and we couldn't have been treated better.

Despite visiting during peak hours (10am on a Sunday) my partner and I were seated immediately. Granted, we weren't picky about sitting by the door. The service was really speedy and our food came quickly. Everything was delicious.
Love this place! I miss living in the Eugene/ Springfield area since this was one of the best inexpensive restaurants around. The breakfast is amazing. Great service too!

The food is amazingly delicious. A perfect balance of vegan and non vegan options; EVERYONE can find something on the menu that they'll love. The place is very popular; there's usually a wait. We had to wait almost 40 minutes but it was totally worth it. Two different waitresses helped us and a third checked us out. All three were lovely. Can't wait to go back.

I have been a loyal customer for 4 yrs and always feel good after eating here. Good healthy food and good service. I will say that my Claire Bear potato shell had been burnt beyond edible twice but has been dealt with in full both times with replacement and still remains my favorite.
I love morning glory 🌞💫💕it's some of the best breakfast yummys I have ever had. And the staff is super friendly and awesome as well. 🌟

Been going for years and always hits the spot. The Hot Link sandwich is spicy and delicious.
Edit: now that they're out of business I crave a good hot link sandwich. Life is hard.

It's a great restaurant with a unique menu for Eugene. Best menu design ever! Food seems authentic and in good serving sizes. Almost always busy with a line out the door so we hardly ever go. Caught a break on a summer afternoon with tables to spare. Great service - remember this tip: they'll tell you the black eyed peas are not spicy but they are!

Love the atmosphere. We are here celebrating our 9 year anniversary. My husband and I. Georgia Peach drink is fabulous. Also very strong. Can definitely feel the moonshine. Smells amazing, staff is friendly, food is out of this world with flavor. Can also find this place on diners drive ins and dives with Guy Fiery.

We LOVE Papa's Soul. Their food is consistently delicious and hits our cravings. Reasonable portions and prices. Our favorites are their mac and cheese, which is to die for, they're Soul Burger (pork patty), and their pulled pork. They are always packed and there's almost always a wait to be seated, so plan for that. Also has an awesome atmosphere & great service!

Top 3 restaurant in all of Eugene. The food is beyond amazing, especially the ribs, the corn and the bread pudding (with bourbon sauce). Be sure to order a fizzle from the bar- so bomb! The wait can be very long, but it is definitely worth it every single time.

Pastries are very good and they have a wide range to choose from. Good coffee too. Can be busy at times, so before you order, make sure you'll have a place to sit. Best place to sit is outside, weather permitting. Would give it 5 stars if it wasn't for the noisy interior, which makes conversation difficult. Some sort of sound dampening decor might help.

I was home visiting from out of state & daughter and granddaughter decided to celebrate granddaughter's birthday a week early so I could be there. I drive down to Sweet Life from Albany to pick up a delicious vegan carrot cake for the birthday party along with vegan cupcakes.  Everything in the looked and smelled terrific. They did a fabulous job decorating the birthday cake. Really wish I had their recipe for that carrot cake 😉

Great pastry, many vegetarian options, but if you're a strict vegan, there are no vegan options, as some have stated.
Sweet Life is up-front about their use of refined sugar. That being said, if that's not an issue, go for it. You'll not find a better quality product anywhere.

I feel like some of the desserts are really good and then some of them are just okay. Some of them are good price and some of them are way overpriced. Always plan on waiting a little bit in line if you go. All the stuff that you really want to eat is usually only available if you but the whole thing. In other words you have to buy the whole cheesecake or the whole cake or the whole pie. They still have a good selection of other things that you can try though. Everything I wanted to try I had to buy the whole dang thing and I didn't want to buy the whole dang thing.
Amazing local favorite for all things dessert and pastry. They also have delicious quiche and gluten-free biscuits and gravy for breakfast! What more could you ask for!?

I just had the best experience at Lucky Noodle. My friend got engaged today and we were celebrating with their parents. We decided to go to Lucky Noodle because they have amazing gluten free options and drinks. We had gotten there and they said they were not able to seat us (It was 7 PM). We explained to them that our friend had just gotten engaged a few hours ago and we were excited to celebrate there. They went and asked if they could seat us. They were able to fit us in. They were so attentive while we waited a few minutes for them to get our table ready. They even brought us out free appetizers while we waited! They did explain that we would need to wait a while until we were able to order due to the Kitchen being backed up. They were so apologetic and said drinks were on the house. We didn't even mind waiting since we didn't want to go anywhere else. Dinner was amazing and our server was so nice and attentive. In the end it turns out that their system had gone down and said our meals were on the house.

I had never heard of this place, until one of the owner called me up because he needed his iPhone screen repaired (I do mobile repair on Apple Devices).  Sounded like kind of a "Eugene" place to eat by just the name I thought.  As soon as I walked in the building I was super impressed. I found this Cafe to be very eloquent.  They had plenty of comfortable seating, a full service bar, and a great atmosphere! Also from just what I observed their customer service is awesome, which is a big deal for me since I too run my own business.  Their employees are super friendly and the owners are on the floor at all times.  It's great! I have not yet had an opportunity to go back and try the food, but I did happen to try their strawberry lemonade which was the best lemonade I have every had! I highly recommend anyone who has read this far to try it!  Anyways, 5 stars for me and I will definitely be going back!

Lucky noodle seems to have completely fallen from grace . Walked in with a friend and it was completely dead. The young guy at the bar seemed to be completely incompetent. He had no idea how to make the two simple drinks we ordered. fruit flies outnumbered everyone in the restaurant by about 20 to 1 . I used to enjoy coming here for the food, ambiance, drinks and service. Unfortunately, not one of those traits are alive at the newly owned and amateurly operated lucky noodle .
Very good breakfast. I'm not sure if they just started serving breakfast, but when we got there at 10:30 it was dead. But the Benedict was perfect and the service great.
Stellar service, great drinks, awesome people. It seems Lucky Noodle is becoming better every day. Was a bit busy when I arrived so I had to wait for my food but didn't mind. Thanks!

What a fun and unique dining experience. Dining is in refurbished train cars. The service and food are stellar. The wine list has a wide array of Willamette Valley wines (and those from around the world too). The shrimp and grits was tasty and expertly prepared. I had the chocolate peanut bar for dessert and it was the perfect bite.

We came here to celebrate Christmas with our employees. It was a very yummy dinned! The crab cakes were so good and the desserts are amazing! Definitely worth the money. It is also pretty fun to dine in a train car.

We went in for a couple drinks but ended up ordering the mud pie. Seating in the lounge is comfortable and light.  Service was fast. Ample parking off to side of building. Mud pie is deadly...two of us couldn't finish one piece. Drinks aren't cheap, but what is anymore?
Loved this place.  Good food, great atmosphere, reasonable prices!  Great place for a special occasion. Dress up or go casual either way you fit in.
This place is amazing. Been around as long as I can remember.  Amazing food and atmosphere.  Lunch here is super affordable. If you are looking for fine dining.  No where is better.
They carry a small amount of produce and have a jewelry booth. They also have an excellent in house restaurant that serves authentic Mexican food.
I recommend the taqueria. Delicious and amazing costumer  service.
Everything you want for Latinx food, cheapissimo prices.
Best fresh marinated meats in town.
this is the best place to eat in town.

The feel of this store is so great. The staff are very friendly and helpful. They pack a lot of selection into a medium-sized space, but it’s not too difficult or overwhelming to navigate. There’s a sale area in the back of the produce section where everything is half off, which is both a great deal and a laudable effort to reduce food waste. This is pretty much my main grocery store.

I have been going to Sundance since I was 10-12 years old? Nothing has changed in the last 15 years except for my location.
I live in Portland but still always plan enough time to swing by Sundance every time I’m in Eugene or even just passing through town!
They’re well worth the detour 😉

Their salad bar and warm food bar is the best!! They also have a great bulk section and medicinal products. Every time I’m here I end up buying multiple stickers to put on my hydroflask or to give to friends/family.
Highly recommend this place! Wish I had a Sundance here in Portland!
Small, but they carry a lot of vegan stuff/fresh produce and staff is really friendly! The food bar/vegan deli stuff is BOMB and worth every cent 👌🏻 Seriously, go check them out!

Spendy place to buy grocery's but if you're into organic and local, this is the place for you. I always like to stop in and see what wines are on sale.  They have a good selection of gluten free foods and all sort of natural products for a wide range of suppliers. The deli on site provides all sorts of food for a quick meal. They also have a pretty decent selection of supplements.

I've been shopping at Sundance for a while, and the service is hit-and-miss. After my most recent experience, though, I will not return. 

The cashier didn't say anything to me at all, just frowned a lot. She watched with annoyance as I bagged my groceries (I am old and slow—it takes me a while to get things together). Did she bother to help me...just to get the line moving a bit faster? No. Not at all.

When the transaction was complete, she turned to the next customer and started tossing their groceries onto my pile of food. She didn't bother to say anything to them, either.

For the prices you pay here, you'd hope for a little kindness, a little decency. I don't ask for much.

Eugene has a lot of health food stores. Guess I'll just drive my slow, old self a little further to spend my money at one of their competitors.
